<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3503] The obr page in the webconsole does not update on refresh</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3503</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the Bundle Repositories are refreshed via the webconsole &quot;OSGi Repository&quot;, the repository is refreshed in the felix environment and the new data is send back to the webpage. However, the new data is not displayed in the webpage, as the reply from felix is ignored in the obr.js javascript file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch below will fix this, by inserting the available data from the reply in the obrData internal datastructurre, before updating the UI.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ol&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;ol&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Eclipse Workspace Patch 1.0&lt;br/&gt;
#P org.apache.felix.webconsole-3.1.8&lt;br/&gt;
Index: src/main/resources/res/ui/obr.js&lt;br/&gt;
===================================================================&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ol&gt;
		&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;src/main/resources/res/ui/obr.js	(revision 1228192)&lt;br/&gt;
+++ src/main/resources/res/ui/obr.js	(working copy)&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -63,7 +63,12 @@&lt;br/&gt;
         $.post(pluginRoot, 
{
             &apos;action&apos; : action,
             &apos;url&apos;    : url
-        }
&lt;p&gt;, renderData, &apos;json&apos;);&lt;br/&gt;
+        }, function(data) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;Unknown macro: {+        	for (var par in data) {
+        		obrData[par]=data[par];
+        	};+        	renderData();+        	}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;, &apos;json&apos;);&lt;br/&gt;
     }&lt;br/&gt;
 }&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

</description>
